-- Roesler Says German Companies Prepared for Crises, Bild Reports
-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 2012-07-27T22:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-27/roesler-says-german-companies-prepared-for-crises-bild-reports.html
Germany  companies are well prepared
for any potential crisis, Economy Minister Philipp Roesler,  Bild 
reported in a preview of an article to appear today.  Roesler added that Germany’s economy remains robust, even
if the debt crisis has undoubtedly increased risks, and the
nation’s companies have innovative products and are competitive,
the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Kraus in Geneva at 
